						<summary>

						<p>On a broken stone lying before the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>1666 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1589, Prabha, Śrāvaṇa ba. 2. The name of the cyclic year appears to have been engraved wrongly for Parābhava. If so, it corresponds to Śaka 1589, current. The details may thus be equated to 1666 A.D., August 6, though they cannot be verified.</p>						

						<p>Except for the invocation to Gaṇādhipati in the beginning, followed by the date, the rest of the inscription is obliterated.</p>						

						</summary>
